    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so if the goal is to be \"disciplined\" and \"objective,\" does that mean originalism is actually a more reliable way to interpret the law than living constitutionalism? or do you think one is objectively better than the other for a modern society?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
